id: pm-8wwl
title: pm init footer + bundle calendar so cal/templates are discoverable
description: "Dogfood 2026-05-17: brand-new agents miss `pm cal`/`pm calendar` because the package is not bundled and `pm --help` lists nothing about installing it. Suggest: (a) print a 5-line next-steps footer at the end of `pm init` listing core invocations and the single-command install for calendar/templates/guide-shell, (b) ship calendar in the default install (it is already the de-facto path for context.agenda) so `pm cal` works out of the box.\n\nAcceptance: pm init prints the footer; calendar command works in a fresh tracker without explicit install; tests assert both."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,bootstrap,calendar,init,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-17T05:49:50.840Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T08:15:38.035Z"
deadline: "2026-05-24T05:49:50.840Z"
author: claude-code-agent
resolution: "Implemented pm-8wwl: pm init now emits next_steps array with discoverability hints (pm create, pm list, pm context, pm install calendar/templates/guide-shell, PM_AUTHOR guidance). When --with-packages was used, hints shift to 'pm cal/templates/guide'."
expected_result: "Expected result: closure includes explicit resolution metadata and verifiable delivery evidence."
actual_result: "Actual result: Implemented pm-8wwl: pm init now emits next_steps array with discoverability hints (pm create, pm list, pm context, pm install calendar/templates/guide-shell, PM_AUTHOR guidance). When --with-packages was used, hints shift to 'pm cal/templates/guide'."
